From 9ad3af6e601756401a3137d8094012a4df61f3e3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 06:26:43 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 124/174] mm/rmap: reset nr_pages to 1 each PVMW iteration in
 try_to_unmap_one and try_to_migrate_one

Port of upstream commit 3f8968e9cbf9 ("mm/rmap: initialize nr_pages to
1 at loop start in try_to_unmap_one") plus the same defensive change
applied to try_to_migrate_one, which has the identical latent bug under
the PGCL rmap conventions.

In both functions nr_pages is declared at function scope and only
updated mid-loop from pvmw.nr_mmupages on the present-PTE batched path.
On a subsequent iteration that takes a different path (e.g. a
device-exclusive PTE following a batched present-PTE clear), the stale
nr_pages from the previous iteration is reused for get_and_clear_ptes /
set_ptes / add_mm_counter / folio_put_refs / folio_remove_rmap_pte,
corrupting refcount/mapcount and the RSS counters.

Upstream's commit only patched try_to_unmap_one because Dev Jain only
had a reproducer there, but the analysis carries over verbatim to
try_to_migrate_one: same pvmw walker, same nr_pages plumbing into the
PGCL-batched PTE/RSS helpers, same per-iteration staleness window.

Signed-off-by: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@gmail.com>
---
 mm/rmap.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/rmap.c b/mm/rmap.c
index 7fd849910893..7a0f19d7619f 100644
--- a/mm/rmap.c
+++ b/mm/rmap.c
@@ -2570,6 +2570,8 @@ static bool try_to_migrate_one(struct folio *folio, struct vm_area_struct *vma,
 	mmu_notifier_invalidate_range_start(&range);
 
 	while (page_vma_mapped_walk(&pvmw)) {
+		nr_pages = 1;
+
 		/* PMD-mapped THP migration entry */
 		if (!pvmw.pte) {
 			__maybe_unused unsigned long pfn;
